Certainly! Below is a simple C# program that prints "Hello World" multiple times using a `for` loop. You can adjust the `repeatCount` variable to change how many times "Hello World" is printed.

```csharp
using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        int repeatCount = 5; // Change this to print more or fewer times

        for (int i = 0; i < repeatCount; i++)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Hello World");
        }
    }
}
```

In this example, "Hello World" will be printed 5 times. You can modify the `repeatCount` variable to any number you wish to print "Hello World" that many times.
